<paragraph blockId="11.[151,676,1798,1824]" box="[151,676,1798,1824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">
<heading box="[151,676,1798,1824]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="11" pageNumber="49" reason="3">
<taxonomicName authority="(Burt) Gilb." box="[151,676,1798,1824]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Phanerochaete" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="49" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="fuscomarginata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Phanerochaete fuscomarginata</emphasis>
(Burt) Gilb.
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1869,2011]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">
The species is characterized by the presence of leptocystidia, ellipsoid basidiospores about 6–8 × 
<quantity box="[1314,1431,1869,1895]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="4.25" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5–5 µm</quantity>
, and brown subicular hyphae with scattered single clamp-connections. Basidiospores are variable in size in the examined specimens, and usually vary from hyaline to pale brown. It has been reported from North America (
<bibRefCitation author="Burdsall, H. H. Jr." box="[159,327,1985,2011]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 165" refId="ref8129" refString="Burdsall, H. H. Jr. (1985) A contribution to the taxonomy of the genus Phanerochaete (Corticiaceae, Aphyllophorales). Mycologia Memoir 10: 1 - 165." type="journal article" year="1985">Burdsall 1985</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[392,495,1985,2011]" name="Uruguay" pageId="11" pageNumber="49">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
in South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Gazzano, S." box="[724,899,1985,2011]" pageId="11" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref8195" refString="Gazzano, S. (1994) Notas sobre Basidiomycetes xilofilos del Uruguay. VI. Nuevos registros. Comunicaciones Botanicas del Museo de Historia Natural de Montevideo 102: 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1994">Gazzano 1994</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
